items.name: Genshin impact - Eula
items.description:
V2

(请阅读，非常重要！Please read,Very important!)

中文

学习归来后的新版本，更像原本的形象了。但可惜的是这个模型并没有达到我的期望。添加触发词可以获得更好的输出，也可以去掉衣服类词汇来更换衣服。推荐权重0.8，换衣服时适当降低权重至0.6以下。可惜之处在于该模型对于裸漏表现并不是很好，经常会出现原服装的衣袖、衣领和紧身裤。对于比基尼类服装乃至全裸，需要添加"collarbone"来去除她的衣领，"sleeveless"去除衣袖，甚至降低权重至0.4。但降低权重后她的发型发色有可能改变，有需要添加"blue short hair"来强化这一概念。如果你只是想要她的默认服装，那这个lora非常适合你，但如果想要给她穿不同的衣服，那你可能需要花点心思多尝试几次。太可惜了。比基尼类大面积裸露可以比较下两个示例图像，自己适当调整prompt。

English

After learning the new version after returning, the model can output more like the original image. But alas this model did not live up to my expectations. Adding trigger words can get better output, and you can also remove clothes words to change clothes. The recommended weight is 0.8, and the weight should be appropriately reduced to below 0.6 when changing clothes. It's a pity that the model doesn't perform very well with nudity, often showing sleeves, collars and tights from the original clothing. For bikini-like clothing or even full nudity, you need to add "collarbone" to remove her collar, "sleeveless" to remove her sleeves, and even lower the weight to 0.4. But after reducing the weight, her hairstyle and hair color may change, and it is necessary to add "blue short hair" to strengthen this concept. If you just want her default outfit, this lora is perfect for you, but if you want to dress her differently, you may need to try a few more times. What a pity.For large-scale exposure in bikinis, you can compare the next two sample images and adjust the prompt accordingly.

items.description:

Size : 1.90 meters; Weight : 150 kilograms; Character : Funny, generous, naive; Favourite food : Gloubi-boulga.

Since 1982 and the end of the show, Casimir has gone through several difficult periods of violence, sex, drugs and rock & roll.

This model is trained with SFW sources only. If you get NSFW content, you're a sick bastard.

You can support me here to be able to render better models (https://ko-fi.com/djo226). Supporters may request model.

items.name: Bonk [style and characters]
items.description:
If you want a more traditional lora experience i recommend the 576 version of the lora.

This is a model trained on bonk's style and most of bonk's esix portfolio of imagery. This model is intended to be used with fluffyrock derivative models such as Omega mix, which can be found in my user profile. This lora works best when combined with other artists to give visual structure to the image, such is the weakness/strength of style selective models such as fluffyrock.

Note that i have added the term "eyeliner" to associate the heavy colored eyelashes of bonk's style. you may need to use "eyeliner eyelashes" inorder to get them to really pop

I might do a training on nai at some point.

Remember that my representational images are non exhaustive and that creativity is the onus of the user of the lora.

Enjoy.

items.name: WW1 - British Soldier uniform
items.description:
How to use

This model has been trained on base SD 1.5. It should be compatible with almost any checkpoint although quality may vary. It works with male or female characters. You can invoke it with the keyword "ww1brit". The LoRA weight depends heavily on what you want to do so it's hard to recommend something specific, I would say from 0.5 to 1 give the best results in normal scenarios. Playing with the CFG scale and hires fix is recommended.

Historical accuracy

This LoRA is mostly based on photographs of reenactors, specifically on WW1 British uniforms while avoiding WW2 uniforms that are pretty similar. There are some instances in the dataset where an American uniform was used so some insignia can appear.

Dataset

Images of costumes, cosplays, reenactments and original photographs from the war were used. A total of 16 images were used.

I plan to make other LoRA themed about World War 1 so don't hesitate to give advice and feedback!

items.name: Felipe Pantone Style
items.description:
Felipe Pantone is an Argentine-Spanish contemporary artist known for his bold and dynamic artwork that merges elements of street art, graffiti, and geometric abstraction.

His style can be described as futuristic, vibrant, and highly energetic. Pantone's work often combines geometric shapes, gradients, and optical illusions, creating visually striking and mesmerizing compositions. He explores the relationship between technology, color, and movement, infusing his art with a sense of dynamism and a futuristic aesthetic.

Pantone is particularly recognized for his use of bold and vibrant colors, often employing neon hues and metallic finishes to create a sense of depth and intensity. His artwork frequently incorporates elements of digital and glitch aesthetics, blurring the lines between the physical and digital realms.

The influence of street art and graffiti is evident in Pantone's work, as he often incorporates elements of typography and graphic design, along with references to urban culture and visual language.

His art can be found in various forms, from large-scale murals adorning public spaces to gallery exhibitions and installations. Pantone's work transcends traditional artistic boundaries, merging contemporary techniques and styles to create a visually captivating and immersive experience.

Felipe Pantone's art captures the spirit of the digital age and urban landscapes, exploring themes of technology, perception, and the rapid pace of modern life. His ability to fuse different artistic disciplines and create visually dynamic compositions has made him a prominent figure in the contemporary art scene.

items.description:
‼ IMPORTANT ‼

  • Your voice matters! Show your support and leave a post, comment and most importantly a review! ⭐

  • Custom LORAs available upon request. Just buymeacoffee.☕

  • This is now a + LORA! (details in workflow advice below) 👇(workflow advice below) 👇

📝Biography📝

(generation advice below) 👇

🌟Melena Maria Rya🌟

also known as Maria Ryabushkina, was born on April 16, 1990, in Moscow, Russia. She grew up in a small town near Moscow and had a relatively normal childhood. In her teenage years, she moved to Moscow to study at university, but she dropped out to pursue a career in modeling.

Rya's modeling career took off in 2010 when she was discovered by a photographer on social media. She quickly gained popularity due to her striking looks and exceptional modeling skills. She has modeled for several fashion brands and has appeared in many magazines and photo shoots.

Outside of modeling, Rya enjoys traveling, fitness, and spending time with friends and family. She currently resides in Moscow and continues to work in the modeling industry, where she has established herself as a prominent figure and a source of inspiration for many young models.

💡Workflow Advice💡

🔧Prompt and Sampling🔧

  • What's the + for?

    • Just an easy way to indicate the dataset image for this particular LORA was based off a minimum of 1024px+ quality source images with the LORA trained at 1024,1024 (I may go higher in the future if I can get a properly working configuration).

    • For the most part, you can start with higher base resolutions to capture more details and/or generate higher quality outputs. See some of the gallery examples.

    • You don't have to gen at high resolution, low res generations will be better quality as well.

  • Most images have been generated with LORA weighted @ .75 - 1.1.

  • For photoreal shots, I've found sampling steps best well above 50 give better results.

  • ControlNet is your friend. Embrace the dark side.😈

    • Tile pre-sample and model is good for extreme close ups

    • I use segmentation for lots of my generations now.

🗒️Side Notes🗒️

  • This + series is something new, let me know if I should take the extra time it takes to create these type of LoRAs or just stick with the regular quality.

  • Help me help you: Leave a review if you've used this LORA.

  • Most of my gens are not voodoo or outside of workflows I've indicated here or in my other posts.

    • In other words: Leave a comment if you are having issues getting good output, I'll try to respond with suggestions.

items.name: In container: in box / in bottle / in fishbowl / in trash can / in suitcase / in bag / in locker ...
items.description:
The goal of this LoHa (simply called lora below) is to improve the "in container" concept ingeneral

---
The image of 'in trunk' and 'in suitcase' get removed for some reason (maybe I should mark my post as mature?)
Therefore I decided to instead put the images here for those who are interested: in trunk, in suitcase
---
As expected, concept lora is much more difficult to made and is more fragile to model switch

This LoHa is trained on ACertainy with clip skip 1 (but you can use both clip skip 1 and 2; see the the last two example images), and chances are it may not work correctly if you use a model that is far away

In face of this issue, here are some tips for the use of this lora

  1. One common strategy is to lower the weight of lora. While this might reduce some weird artifacts, the success rate of getting the concept right also decreases.

  2. You can first generate some images on ACertainty with txt2img, and then you use img2img on another model. This is what I did with the refrigerator image. You probably still need to lower lora weight in the second stage.

  3. What I do personally is to use some merge that is close to ACertainty. This is done through add difference merge with other model: AC+w(model1-model2)

Do you really need this lora?

In fact, many of these concepts can already be generated directly with the popular models. This is for example the case for 'in cup', 'in bowl', and 'in box'.

Moreover, there are several existing loras on civitai for similar things, and they may suit better your need depending on what you want to achieve (just search in box or in container/in-container).

However, for some other concepts, such as 'in suitcase' or 'in bag', it may be much easier with this lora, unless you are very good at prompting and know how to achieve it directly on your model. Apparently, the effect of the lora on each model is different, so the only way to see whether it makes a difference is to try is yourself.

More details on each sub-concepts

General advice: When you want to put a person in a small thing, adding chibi, mini person, minigirl could help. Fetal position is another tag that could be relevant in general.

  • 'In container' is a general tag that you can, and probably should always put

  • 'In suitcase', 'in bag', 'in closet', 'in bottle', 'in refrigerator', and 'in basket' seem to work the best and improve over what the base model know.

  • For 'in box', 'in bucket', 'in bowl', and 'in cup', it is more difficult to say whether using this lora really makes a difference, as most model can already do them.

  • 'In trash can' works quite well but it is overfitted on Miyu from blue archive.

  • 'In trunk' works but is overfitted and it never knows the right size of a human compared to a car.

  • 'In locker', 'in sack', and 'in cage' are more difficult to played with we hardly get good results

items.name: Kurosu Gatari  / Siberian Hahasky (Style)
items.description:
Based on the art of Kurosu Gatari/Siberian Hahasky.

Split into two versions! I was informed that Siberian Hahasky is just an alias used by Kurosu Gatari, so I updated my LoRA.

The Siberian Hahasky (originally v 1.0) version is still mostly trained with his works featuring mostly one mother under his Siberian Hahasky alias.

The Kurosu Gatari version is new and trained with most of his other works for variety, but still includes some of the Hahasky dataset.

Remember to support them if you enjoy their art!

If you want to support me buy me a coffee!

Weight: 0.8-1.1 for Siberian Hahasky, 1-1.4 for Kurosu Gatari
Triggerwords: None.

Notes for Siberian Hahasky version:

  • Description of the character needs to be pretty detailed, otherwise it will mostly create the same character, as most of their illustrations are of the same character as of now. Will probably update it as they put out more content.

  • Works pretty well with character LoRAs, making them more motherly/mature.

  • Going above 1.1 in weight is not recommended, as it often results in Manga panels appearing.

Notes for the Kurosu Gatari version:

  • Still a slight bias towards the mother, but not nearly as dominant.

Feel free to share some of the pictures you create with me and post them here!

items.name: Wang Liu Mei - Gundam00
items.description:
A nice waifu that committed the greatest possible sin... I don't mean going batshit insane, that part is ok. My problem with her is that she received the "Hinata treatment" (did the useless Boruto suck her boobs dry?) in other words she was revised down so she could become plain and boring after the timeskip.

Anyway here we have the cute pretimeskip no quite yet fully batshit insane Wang Liu Mei.

Had ok results with: <lora:G00WangLiuMei:0.55>, G00WangLiuMei, large_breasts, twin_braids, twintails,

Putting single_braid as a negative might help to keep her hairstyle stable.

Seem there are only images with her signature outfit so you might have trouble making it spit something else, otherwise the Lora seems stable enough through all the range.

For available outfits there just her common outfit which can be invoked with: WLMOutfit

It seems that invoking her outfit might spit the correct print of her dress and make it the long skirt version. Without invoking it you will get a more generic version and very likely the miniskirt version of it.

I will add the tags summary inside the dataset so people can experiment.

I might do an alternative version in the future without pruning her outfit tags, it will be harder to reproduce her classic outfit accurately but should decrease the bias towards it.
